-- Carnegie Wave Energy Wins State Grant for Australian Desalination Project
-- Baldave Singh
-- 2010-07-27T06:52:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-27/carnegie-wind-wins-government-grant-for-australian-desalination-project.html

          
          
             Carnegie Wave Energy Ltd. , the
Australian marine energy project developer, has won A$250,000
($226,000) in government funding for a trial desalination
project it aims to integrate with wave-power technology.  
 The National Centre of Excellence in Desalination selected
the project from among 61 applicants and will provide half the
funding for the A$500,000 project, Carnegie said in a  statement 
on its website yesterday. Carnegie will provide the other half.  
 The project will be based at NCED headquarters at
Rockingham, south of Perth, close to Carnegieâ€™s Perth Wave
Energy Project site, where Carnegie is testing technology for
generating electricity. Carnegie eventually plans to integrate
the two projects.  
